
[1]preferment

   PREFER'MENT, n. Advancement to a higher office, dignity or station.
   Change of manners and even of character often follows preferment. A
   profligate life should be considered a disqualification for preferment,
   no less than want of ability.

   1. Superior place or office. All preferments should be given to
   competent men.

   2. Preference. [Not used.
